 source of energy, , WWF Germany, Frankfurt am Main; (1996) Climate Change 1995: The science of climate change: contribution of working group I to the second assessment of the intergovernmental panel on climate change, , IPCC, Cambridge University Press, UK, J.T. Houghton, L.G. Meira Filho, B.A. Callender, N. Harris, A. Kattenberg, K. Maskell (Eds.); Sheehan, J., Camobreco, V., Duffield, J., Graboski, M., Shapouri, H., (1998) Life cycle inventory of biodiesel and petroleum diesel for use in an urban bus, p. 314. , Golden: National Renewable Energy Laboratory, NREL/SR- 580-24089; Gover, M.P., Collings, S.A., Hitchcock, G.T., Moon, D.P., Wilkins, G.T., (1996) Alternative road transport fuels-a preliminary life-cycle study for the UK, 1-2. , HMSO, London, ETSU-R-92; Ecobilan Bilans énergétiques et gaz à effet de serre des filières de production de biocarburants Paris: ADEME/DIREM. Rapport d'après les travaux d'Ecobilan PricewaterhouseCoopers, p. 39. , 2002.11.132p, rapport d'annexes et note de synththèse 17p; Elsayed, M.A., Matthews, R., Mortimer, N.D., (2003) Carbon and energy balances for a range of biofuels options, , Project number B/B6/00784/REP, Resources Research Unit Sheffield Hallam University; Fehrenbach, H., (2008) GHG Accounting methodology and default data according to the biomass sustainability ordinance (BSO). 2nd GBEP task force meeting on GHG methodologies, , UN Foundation-WashingtonD.C, 6-7 March; (2008) Carbon and sustainability reporting within the renewable transport fuel obligation requirements and guidance. Government recommendation to the Office of the Renewable Fuels Agency, , http://www.dft.gov.uk/pgr/roads/environment/rtfo/, Department of Transport, Available at; Beer, T., Grant, T., Morgan, G., Lapszewicz, J., Anyon, P., Nelson, P., (2001) Comparison of transport fuels. Final report (EV45A/2/F3C) to the Australian Greenhouse Office on the Stage 2 study of life cycle emissions analysis if alternative fuels for heavy vehicles, , CSIRO; Rollefs